The '''UAE International Award for Poets of Peace''' was launched on 1 May 2014 at the [[International Humanitarian City]] (IHC) in [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dd1EC1FGCko | title=UAE International Award for Poets of Peace Launched – City7 TV | website=[[YouTube]] | accessdate=22 February 2015 }}</ref> It is the first award of its kind, bridging a multitude of nationalities and languages in which poets will present their sonnets, spreading a message of peace around the world.{{fact|date=February 2015}} The global award plan at using poetry to disseminate consciousness amongst people about the importance of peace and raises further awareness for humanitarian work around the world.
==Objectives== The Award has the following objectives:{{fact|date=February 2015}} # Promote the peace message to the world # Spread the culture of peace across the world # Raise awareness for humanitarian work around the world # Support world relief programs.
==Vision== The Award has the following vision:{{fact|date=February 2015}} # Sending a message to the world about the need to stop war and combat hunger # Unifying world peace in one entity bound by peace, without discrimination on race or religion, & spreading the message of love, unity and peace.
